shit: 1:1: warning: A local outside a function has no scope to bind, declare the variable plainly or move it into a function.
     1 |  local --help
       |  ^~~~~ here.
DESCRIPTION
  The local builtin declares each named variable local to the current function,
  so the value it had in the caller returns when the function ends, and it
  assigns a value when name=value is given. It is an error outside a function.

SYNOPSIS
  local [-aAilnrux] name[=value] ...

OPTIONS
      --help              Display help.
  -a                      Declare an indexed array.
  -A                      Declare an associative array.
  -i                      Mark an integer whose every assignment evaluates as
                          arithmetic.
  -l                      Accepted without effect.
  -n                      Accepted without effect.
  -r                      Accepted without effect.
  -u                      Accepted without effect.
  -x                      Accepted without effect.
rc=0
